ehensive indices that map out the terminology and style of the translation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn Arabic.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEpidemicsvEarly works to 1800. 4aAntike Medizin. 4aArabistik. 4aGalen. 4aMedizingeschichte.  aArabistic.  aGalen.  aHistory of medicine.  aMedicine in antiquity.1 aVagelpohl, Uwe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311077318740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110774986zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110774986zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110774986/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-GOA